'''Holding the man''' is an infringement in the game of [[Australian rules football]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadspin.com/the-complete-guide-to-understanding-australian-rules-fo-1795130938|title=The Complete Guide To Understanding Australian Rules Football|last=Tippett|first=Ben|work=Deadspin|access-date=2017-12-13|language=en-US}}</ref> This occurs when a player is tackling his opponent without the ball. If the team whose player committed the infringement plays on, then a [[free kick (Australian rules football)|free kick]] will be awarded. However, if the team whose player was tackled without the ball plays on, then the advantage is paid.

