'''Kråmyra Stadion''' was a [[association football|football]] stadium in the city of [[Ålesund]], in [[Norway]] that served as the home grounds for [[Aalesunds FK]] from 1977 until [[Color Line Stadium]] opened in April, 2005. It had a capacity of 11,000 people. The venue has hosted [[Norway national under-21 football team]] matches twice, playing 0–5 against [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden]] on 8 August 1972 and 3–1 against [[Finland national under-21 football team|Finland]] on 27 April 1982.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fotball.no/System-pages/TabellTermin/?tournamentId=39901 |title=Norge Menn U21 |publisher=[[Football Association of Norway]] |language=Norwegian |archivedate=26 November 2011 |accessdate=26 November 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63UG3Ayfy?url=http://www.fotball.no/System-pages/TabellTermin/?tournamentId=39901 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>

