'''Roy Henzell Oval''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Caloundra]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]]. The first recorded match on the ground came in 1981 when Queensland Country played the touring [[West Indies cricket team|West Indians]].<ref name="OTH">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/58_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Roy Henzell Oval, Caloundra|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=20 October 2011}}</ref> It held its only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1993 when [[Queensland cricket team|Queensland]] played the touring [[England A cricket team|England A]] side,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/58_f.html|title=First-Class Matches played on Roy Henzell Oval, Caloundra|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref> with the match ending in a draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/56/56992.html|title=Queensland v England A, 1992/93|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref> Three Youth [[One Day International]]s were played there in 2007 between [[Australia Under-19 cricket team|Australia Under-19s]] and [[Pakistan Under-19 cricket team|Pakistan Under-19]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/58_uo.html|title=Youth One-Day International Matches played on Roy Henzell Oval, Caloundra|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref>
